description: [Status: stable] [Name: unused-private-protocol] [Message: Private protocol {name} is never used] What it does Checks for the presence of unused private typing.Protocol definitions. Why is this bad? A private typing.Protocol that is defined but not used is likely a mistake. It should either be used, made public, or removed to avoid confusion. Example import typing class _PrivateProtocol(typing.Protocol): foo: int Use instead: import typing class _PrivateProtocol(typing.Protocol): foo: int def func(arg: _PrivateProtocol) -> None: ...
